  "texts": [
    "Algorithm 1 Constrained Alignment via Iterative Dualization (CAID)1: Input: reference model π ref, initial dual λ init, reward and utility models: r, {g i } m i = 1, stepsize η, total iteration T, regularization parameter β, and thresholds {b i } m i = 1.",
    "2: Initialization: λ(0) = λ init and π θ ⋆ (0) = π ref.3: for t = 0, 1, 2,..., T -1 do 4:Dual subgradient step:λ(t + 1) = [ λ(t) -η u(λ(t))] +(6)where u(λ(t)) is a subgradient direction (5) using π θ ⋆ (t) (λ(t)).",
    "5:LLM policy optimization step:θ ⋆ (t + 1) ∈ argmax θ ∈ Θ L(π θ, λ(t + 1)).",
    "(7)6: end for 7: Output: {θ ⋆ (t)} T t = 1.",
    "Dual-based constrained alignment methodTo approximate the solution of Problem (U-CA), we show a dual subgradient method for Problem (2) in Algorithm 1."
